Privacy Policy for App Designer
We are pleased that you are using App Designer and take the protection of your data seriously. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, process, and use data when you use our app, specifically regarding the source code of applications created within App Designer.
1. Data Controller
The data controller responsible for processing your information within the meaning of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is:
Norbert Grieger
Email:
xx85192@gmail.com
2. Data Collection and Storage
a. Technical Usage Data: When using App Designer, we may collect technical data such as your operating system, device information, and general usage patterns. This data is stored anonymously and used solely for app improvement purposes.
b. Source Code of Created Apps: We may collect and process this data for analysis and improvement purposes. The source code is stored and processed in an anonymized form and contains no personally identifiable information.
3. Purpose of Data Processing
The data we collect is used exclusively to:
•    Ensure the functionality and stability of the app
•    Make improvements
•    Identify and resolve any technical issues.
4. Lawfulness of Data Processing
The processing of your data is based on your voluntary consent in accordance with Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR. You may withdraw your consent at any time in the app’s settings or by contacting us directly, as outlined below.
5. Data Transfer and Sharing
Your data is not shared with third parties. All processing and analysis are conducted internally, ensuring that the data remains strictly under our control and is used solely to improve our service.
6. Data Retention Period
The collected source code is stored for a maximum period of 90 days. After this period, it is automatically deleted unless it is still required for the purposes mentioned above.
7. Your Rights
Under the GDPR, you have the following rights:
•    Right to access the data we process about you (Art. 15 GDPR),
•    Right to rectification of inaccurate data (Art. 16 GDPR),
•    Right to erasure of your data (Art. 17 GDPR),
•    Right to restrict processing (Art. 18 GDPR),
•    Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR),
•    Right to object to the processing of your data (Art. 21 GDPR),
•    Right to withdraw consent at any time (Art. 7(3) GDPR).
To exercise your rights, please contact us using the details provided in section 1.
8. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to amend this Privacy Policy as necessary to comply with legal requirements or changes in our data processing practices.
9. Contact Information
If you have any questions regarding the collection, processing, or use of your data, or if you wish to exercise any of your rights, please contact me:
Norbert Grieger
Email:
xx85192@gmail.com